An Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court yesterday ordered two drivers suspected as “one-chance” robbers to be remanded in Kirikiri Prisons for allegedly robbing their passengers of valuables worth N453, 500. Chief Magistrate A. A. Fashola ordered that the suspects, Abayomi Adelabi, 42, Solomon Sunday, 42, to remain in prison custody pending when they perfect their bail conditions. Adelabi and Sunday are facing a three-count charge of conspiracy and robbery. Prosecuting Sergeant Michael Unah told the court that the defendants robbed Mrs Aina Rita and Mrs Florence Atobatele of their valuables worth N453, 500. He said the defendants allegedly blew dried pepper into the eyes of the victims, dispossessed them of their valuables and pushed them out of the moving bus. He listed items stolen from the complainants to include  N314,000 cash, an Itel phone valued at N14, 000, a wedding ring worth N15, 000, power bank valued at N3, 500,  an Infinix phone worth N45, 000, a wedding ring worth N55, 000 and a necklace valued at N7, 000, totalling N453, 500. The prosecutor said that the defendants committed the offences with others still at large on June 18 around 5.30 a.m., at Estate Gate, Ipaja, Lagos. Chief Magistrate Fashola granted the defendants N100, 000 bail each with two sureties each in like sum. He adjourned the case till September 13.